## Conventions

- File names: `kebab-case.tsx`. Components: `PascalCase`. Variant values:
  `kebab-case` lowercase.
- Use `React.forwardRef` for any component wrapping an HTML element.
- Use `cva()` for variant-driven styling — never `if (variant === ...)`
  inside JSX.
- Use `cn()` from `@famm/ui` for className merging.
- Export named prop types (`ButtonProps`), not inline.
- Default exports are reserved for Next.js pages and config files.

## Use semantic HTML

- `<button>` for buttons. Never `<div onClick>`.
- `<a>` for navigation. Never `<button>` styled as a link unless it
  triggers an action.
- `<form>` wraps form controls. Submission goes through `onSubmit`, not
  `onClick` on the button.
- Lists use `<ul>` / `<ol>` / `<li>`. Definition pairs use `<dl>`.
- Headings are sequential: a page has one `<h1>`; sections nest.
- Landmarks: `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<header>`, `<footer>` — one
  `<main>` per page.
- Tables are `<table>` with `<th scope>`. Never grid-divs for tabular data.

## Never (review will reject)

- New component that duplicates an existing one with a different name.
- Variants encoded as boolean props (`<Card raised highlighted compact>`)
  instead of `variant="..."`.
- `className` prop used to override foundational styling (color, padding
  scale, radius) — those come from variants.
- Importing a new component library (shadcn-fork, MUI, Mantine) or icon
  set (we use `lucide-react`).
- Inline SVG when `lucide-react` has the icon.
- `packages/ui` importing from `apps/web` (inverts dependency).
- Files named `Button.tsx`, `Card.tsx`, etc. anywhere in `apps/web/src/`
  that re-implement the existing primitives.

## State coverage — all four, every time

A list or fetch surface must handle:

| State | Required shape |
|-------|----------------|
| Loading | Skeleton matching the final layout. Not a centered spinner unless the surface is < 200px tall. |
| Empty | One sentence + one primary action. |
| Error | Plain-language summary + retry button. Surface details via `<details>` if actionable. |
| Loaded | Content. |

Implement the four in the component, not the page. The page passes
props; it doesn't re-implement states.

